</figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-assemble-your-italian-sausage-casserole">Assemble Your Italian Sausage Casserole</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Preheat</strong>. Preheat your oven to 375°F&nbsp;<em>(190°C/Gas Mark 5)</em>&nbsp;and lightly grease your 2.5-quart casserole or baking dish, or a 9x13 baking pan with extra virgin olive oil.</li>



<li><strong>Prepare pasta. </strong>Boil 16 ounces (<em>454 grams</em>) of pasta according to the package instructions, <strong>minus about 2 minutes for an al denté</strong> <em>(or 'firm to the bite')</em> texture. Drain and rinse the pasta with cool water and transfer it to your prepared casserole or baking dish. </li>



<li><strong>Pour</strong>. Pour your preferred 24 ounces (<em>680 grams</em>) of<strong> <a href="https://bakeitwithlove.com/classic-marinara-sauce-recipe/">marinara</a> or spaghetti sauce</strong> over the cooked pasta.</li>



<li><strong>Add</strong>. Cut 1 pound (<em>454 grams</em>) of Italian sausage links into chunks and layer them over the pasta and sauce, <strong>pushing into the layers below them</strong> until the top is covered.</li>



<li><strong>Top.</strong> Top the casserole with 1 cup (<em>112 grams</em>) of<strong> </strong>shredded mozzarella cheese and/or ¼ cup (<em>25 grams</em>) of Parmesan cheese.</li>



<li><strong>Bake</strong>. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon (<em>15 grams</em>) of fresh, cut basil over the cheese topping. <strong>Bake uncovered at 375°F&nbsp;<em>(190°C/Gas Mark 5)</em> for 35 - 40 minutes</strong> or until bubbling around the edges. The chunks of Italian sausage should have an<a href="https://www.foodsafety.gov/food-safety-charts/safe-minimum-cooking-temperature"> internal temperature of 160ºF <em>(71ºC)</em></a> as read by a digital meat thermometer.</li>



<li><strong>Serve</strong>. Remove from the oven and serve immediately. Garnish with more cheese, basil, or chopped parsley if desired.</li>
</ol>



