				<span class="comment-author-name">Joanne</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">December 18, 2025 at 12:23 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://bakeitwithlove.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
I removed the sausage from the casing and sauteed it with some diced onion and garlic.   Turned out great!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-146148" data-commentid="146148" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-146148" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Joanne" aria-label="Reply to Joanne">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-146333">
	<article id="article-comment-146333">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Angela Latimer</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">December 20, 2025 at 8:49 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Sounds fantastic Joanne, thanks for sharing!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-146333" data-commentid="146333" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-146333" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Angela Latimer" aria-label="Reply to Angela Latimer">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-138781">
	<article id="article-comment-138781">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Stacey</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">October 14, 2025 at 2:38 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://bakeitwithlove.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Absolutely delicious. I would like to add some veggies next time I’m thinking some broccoli florettes. Would I thaw them out or keep them frozen, and at what point would they go into the  mixture?  I feel like if they’re included at the beginning, they would cook too much.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-138781" data-commentid="138781" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-138781" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Stacey" aria-label="Reply to Stacey">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-138828">
	<article id="article-comment-138828">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Angela Latimer</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">October 15, 2025 at 7:04 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>The time and temperature of the casserole are sufficient to cook frozen broccoli but I would recommend to steam or thaw the broccoli first. This should prevent any excess water from the frozen broccoli making your dish soggy. Thanks for asking!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-138828" data-commentid="138828" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-138828" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Angela Latimer" aria-label="Reply to Angela Latimer">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-115011">
	<article id="article-comment-115011">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Joanne</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">April 16, 2025 at 10:09 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://bakeitwithlove.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Turned out great.  Quick and easy.  Delish!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-115011" data-commentid="115011" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-115011" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Joanne" aria-label="Reply to Joanne">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-40967">
	<article id="article-comment-40967">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Aline Terrell</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">October 19, 2023 at 1:56 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://bakeitwithlove.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-4.svg" alt="4 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
This was a very good base recipe.  I added one of the suggested additions, mushrooms.  I assembled things a bit differently, though; I put all the ingredients (including the mozzarella and part of the parmesan, but except the sausage) into a bowl and stirred it up.  For spaghetti sauce, I used Rao's Tomato Basil.  Like one of the other commenters, I also needed more sauce; fortunately, I had part of a jar on hand. My advice is that if you're adding anything to it, use the 32-ounce jar.  After tasting the mixture, I also added two teaspoons of Italian seasoning, a teaspoon of garlic powder and a teaspoon of onion powder.  I sprinkled the fresh basil on top before adding the sausage.</p>
<p>I think the next time I make this (and I will), I'll pre-cook the sausage and cut down on the baking time, or pre-cook the sausage, cover the casserole with aluminum foil before baking, and use the regular time.  Some pieces of sausage got blackened at the ends, and there were some crunchy bits of overbaked pasta in the casserole.  The cut-up sausage was a great and different take on meatballs, and the casserole itself came out very well overall.  Thanks very much!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-40967" data-commentid="40967" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-40967" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Aline Terrell" aria-label="Reply to Aline Terrell">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-24107">
	<article id="article-comment-24107">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Suzanne</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">December 02, 2022 at 8:11 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Liked it but the 24 ounces of sauce was barely enough to cover the<br />
Pasta</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-24107" data-commentid="24107" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-24107" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Suzanne" aria-label="Reply to Suzanne">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="comment-35046">
	<article id="article-comment-35046">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Dave</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">July 17, 2023 at 8:37 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://bakeitwithlove.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
For me it was definitely enough.  I think it may depend on the size of your casserole dish.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-35046" data-commentid="35046" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-35046" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Dave" aria-label="Reply to Dave">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-16049">
	<article id="article-comment-16049">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Betsy</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">August 01, 2022 at 10:16 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>It looks like you didn’t cook the sausage links first - it seems like that would make the dish greasy?  Just looking for clarification!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-16049" data-commentid="16049" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-16049" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Betsy" aria-label="Reply to Betsy">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-16080">
	<article id="article-comment-16080">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Angela @ BakeItWithLove.com</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">August 02, 2022 at 6:50 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>That's correct, the sausage was simply chopped into large pieces and assembled into the casserole (to cook while baking). If you would prefer to cook the sausage before assembling the sausage bake, you can reduce thebaking time of the casserole to 20-25 minutes. Enjoy!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-16080" data-commentid="16080" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-16080" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Angela @ BakeItWithLove.com" aria-label="Reply to Angela @ BakeItWithLove.com">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-6764">
	<article id="article-comment-6764">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Robin Hillyard</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">October 21, 2021 at 4:12 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://bakeitwithlove.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Loved this and will definitely make again.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-6764" data-commentid="6764" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-6764" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Robin Hillyard" aria-label="Reply to Robin Hillyard">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="comment-68868">
	<article id="article-comment-68868">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Daisy</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">August 30, 2024 at 7:49 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Do you remove the casing from the sausage?</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-68868" data-commentid="68868" data-postid="25164" data-belowelement="article-comment-68868" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Daisy" aria-label="Reply to Daisy">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-3" id="comment-68894">
	<article id="article-comment-68894">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Angela Latimer</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">August 31, 2024 at 7:15 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>No, I didn't remove the casings for this casserole. You could, but it isn't necessary. Thanks for asking!</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
